author: Grace Panetta
title: Photos and videos show Wisconsin voters trying to socially distance in line at the polls to cast ballots during a pandemic
description: As dozens of states have postponed their presidential primaries, Wisconsin's Tuesday election is still proceeding as scheduled. After the state legislature refused to delay the election, courts blocked multiple lawsuits and an executive order from Gov. Tony E…
content:
People throughout the state of Wisconsin are arriving to vote at polling locations on Tuesday morning armed with masks and gloves, attempting to practice social distancing while waiting in line possibly for hours.
